<% provide(:title, "Help") %>

<div class="container mb-5">
	<div class="row bg-info card my-4 mb-3 pd-l-2">
		<h3>
		    <span class="fa fa-question-circle text-white pt-2"></span>
		    Frequently asked questions
		</h3>
	</div>
	<div class="row">
	    <p>
	    Below, we answer some the most frequently asked questions on our platform.
	    </p>
  
	    <ul id="accordion" class="col-sm-6 col-md-12">
	        <!-- Question one -->
	        <li>
	            <div id="choose" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne" >
	                <b>It is my first time to sell using this web app, how will you support me during the process?</b>
	                <span class="fas fa-chevron-up fa-1x text-info right-icon-pos pr-3 pt-2"></span>
	            </div>
	            <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-parent="#accordion">
                  <div class="card-body">
                    SUpost is responsible to help you at every step throughout the selling process. Our team made it more user-friendly for were the users can easily manage there posting.
                  </div>
                </div>
	        </li>
	        
	        <!-- Question two -->
	        <li>
	            <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
	                <b>Where do I go incase I have a complaint?</b>
	                <span class="fas fa-chevron-down fa-1x text-info right-icon-pos pr-3 pt-2"></span>
	            </div>
                <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#accordion">
                  <div class="card-body">
                   SUpost is basically  a user generated content site. Hence, we cannot take any action against a person. Web app can only disable account of the fraudster.
                  </div>
                </div>
	        </li>
	        
	        <!-- Question three -->
	        <li>
	            <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
	                <b>What are the rules for sellers?</b>
	                <span class="fas fa-chevron-down fa-1x text-info right-icon-pos pr-3 pt-2"></span>
	            </div>
                <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-parent="#accordion">
                  <div class="card-body">
                    <p>Supost work very hard to make a user-friendly web app marketplace. Our aim is to meet the basic needs of sellers who are registered with us.
                    To keep the quality of service, we have set rules for posting.</p> 
                    <p><b>Failure to keep updated information</b>:- When you list your post on our platform, then it is your responsibility to update the information regularly. You should update the post details such as price, quantity, status, etc</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
	        </li>
	        
	        <!-- Question Four -->
	        <li>
	            <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
	                <b>How can I file a complaint?</b>
	                <span class="fas fa-chevron-down fa-1x text-info right-icon-pos pr-3 pt-2"></span>
	            </div>
                <div id="collapseFour" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFour" data-parent="#accordion">
                  <div class="card-body">
                    File a complaint against fraudster at SUpost customer complaint forum to get a quick solution of complaints, customer may also send email listed in contact section. It will help customer to resolve their complaints.
                  </div>
                </div>
	        </li>
	        
	        <!-- Questiion Five -->
	        <li>
	            <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive">
	                <b>How should I set the best price for my posting?</b>
	                <span class="fas fa-chevron-down fa-1x text-info right-icon-pos pr-3 pt-2"></span>
	            </div>
                <div id="collapseFive" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFive" data-parent="#accordion">
                  <div class="card-body">
                    Sellers can set the price at your choice. However, we recommend to place a reasonable price with the items or services you are selling. It means price shouldn't be too low or too high.  
                  </div>
                </div>
	        </li>
	        
	        <!-- Question Six-->
	        <li>
	            <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseSix" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseSix">
	                <b>Who are all the buyers and where are they from?</b>
	                <span class="fas fa-chevron-down fa-1x text-info right-icon-pos pr-3 pt-2"></span>
	            </div>
                <div id="collapseSix" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#accordion">
                  <div class="card-body">
                    Our buyer's list include range of people from different categories, professions and different lifestyles. It could be any one can buy your items or services all throughout Standford, California.
                  </div>
                </div>
	        </li>
	    </ul>
	</div>
</div>